alification holder is able to:\\n(1) function confidently in digital cultures; \\n(2) understand the history and theory of new media; \\n(3) recognise social media and user practices as e.g. net activism and hacking; \\n(4) apply problem based learning; \\n(5) analyse discourse; \\n(6) write for a research weblog and apply basic programming skills.\"}},\"learningSetting\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-setting/6fd4685715\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-setting/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"formal learning\"}},\"mode\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-assessment/9191af2ed9\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-assessment/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Presential\"}},\"language\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"language\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"English\"}},\"title\":{\"en\":\"Transformations in Digital Cultures\"},\"dcType\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-opportunity/0f7dac46ca\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-opportunity/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Programme module\"}}},\"title\":{\"en\":\"Transformations in Digital Cultures\"}},{\"id\":\"urn:epass:learningAchievement:2\",\"type\":\"LearningAchievement\",\"awardedBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:awardingProcess:1\",\"type\":\"AwardingProcess\",\"awardingBody\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:org:1\",\"type\":\"Organisation\",\"location\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:location:1\",\"type\":\"Location\",\"address\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:address:1\",\"type\":\"Address\",\"countryCode\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}}}},\"logo\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:mediaObject:1\",\"type\":\"MediaObject\",\"content\":\"\",\"contentEncoding\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/encoding/6146cde7dd\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/encoding/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"base64\"}},\"contentType\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type/PNG\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"file-type\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"PNG\"}}},\"vatIdentifier\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:legalIdentifier:2\",\"type\":\"LegalIdentifier\",\"spatial\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}},\"notation\":\"SE202100287401\"},\"altLabel\":{\"en\":\"UMU\"},\"legalName\":{\"en\":\"Umea university\"},\"registration\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:legalIdentifier:2\",\"type\":\"LegalIdentifier\",\"spatial\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}},\"notation\":\"SE202100287401\"},\"homepage\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:webResource:1\",\"type\":\"WebResource\",\"contentURL\":\"http://www.umu.se/english/?languageId=1\"}}},\"influencedBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:activity:2\",\"type\":\"LearningActivity\",\"additionalNote\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:note:5\",\"type\":\"Note\",\"noteLiteral\":{\"en\":\"Bertrand, I., & Hughes, P.(2005). Media Research Methods: Audiences, Institutions, Texts. Basingstoke [etc.]: Palgrave/Macmillan. Booth, W. C., Colomb, G. G., & Williams, J. M. (2003). The Craft of Research. Chicago [etc.]: University of Chicago Press. Stokes, J. (2013). How to Do Media and Cultural Studies. Los Angeles [etc.]: SAGE.\"},\"subject\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:concept:83624db8-8dd0-4ca2-b058-5eba8256bde5\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:conceptScheme:f9c8b229-c537-450b-ab7c-cd6af1146eb8\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Recommended reading\"}}},\"awardedBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:awardingProcess:1\",\"type\":\"AwardingProcess\",\"awardingBody\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:org:1\",\"type\":\"Organisation\",\"location\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:location:1\",\"type\":\"Location\",\"address\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:address:1\",\"type\":\"Address\",\"countryCode\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}}}},\"logo\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:mediaObject:1\",\"type\":\"MediaObject\",\"content\":\"\",\"contentEncoding\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/encoding/6146cde7dd\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/encoding/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"base64\"}},\"contentType\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type/PNG\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"file-type\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"PNG\"}}},\"vatIdentifier\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:legalIdentifier:2\",\"type\":\"LegalIdentifier\",\"spatial\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}},\"notation\":\"SE202100287401\"},\"altLabel\":{\"en\":\"UMU\"},\"legalName\":{\"en\":\"Umea university\"},\"registration\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:legalIdentifier:2\",\"type\":\"LegalIdentifier\",\"spatial\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}},\"notation\":\"SE202100287401\"},\"homepage\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:webResource:1\",\"type\":\"WebResource\",\"contentURL\":\"http://www.umu.se/english/?languageId=1\"}}},\"specifiedBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:learningActivitySpec:2\",\"type\":\"LearningActivitySpecification\",\"mode\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-assessment/9191af2ed9\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/learning-assessment/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Presential\"}},\"language\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/ENG\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"language\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"English\"}},\"title\":{\"en\":\"Research Design\"}},\"description\":{\"en\":\"In this module students draw together what they have learned before and apply their theoretical insights, research methods, and practical skills in order to design their research plan for the second semester thesis. Each of the five first-semester modules emphasised a particular disciplinary and/or theoretical approach and a specific methodology, but always in a problem oriented and interdisciplinary context. In the second semester students develop their own research on developments and issues in contemporary media culture; the research plan supports them in connecting their own research questions and strategies to the previous modules. Students design this research plan in a step-by-step process. These steps are prepared by an introductory lecture. In the first week students explore their thesis topic and discuss their ideas. Students also take part in a workshop on how to peer-review a research proposal. In the subsequent weeks, students support each other by engaging in weekly peer-review sessions in which they critically evaluate the work of their colleagues.\"},\"temporal\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:period:2\",\"type\":\"PeriodOfTime\",\"endDate\":\"2018-03-09T00:00:00+01:00\",\"startDate\":\"2018-02-05T00:00:00+01:00\"},\"title\":{\"en\":\"Research Design\"}},\"provenBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:learningAssessment:2\",\"type\":\"LearningAssessment\",\"awardedBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:awardingProcess:1\",\"type\":\"AwardingProcess\",\"awardingBody\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:org:1\",\"type\":\"Organisation\",\"location\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:location:1\",\"type\":\"Location\",\"address\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:address:1\",\"type\":\"Address\",\"countryCode\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}}}},\"logo\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:mediaObject:1\",\"type\":\"MediaObject\",\"content\":\"\",\"contentEncoding\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/encoding/6146cde7dd\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/encoding/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"base64\"}},\"contentType\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type/PNG\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/file-type\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"file-type\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"PNG\"}}},\"vatIdentifier\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:legalIdentifier:2\",\"type\":\"LegalIdentifier\",\"spatial\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}},\"notation\":\"SE202100287401\"},\"altLabel\":{\"en\":\"UMU\"},\"legalName\":{\"en\":\"Umea university\"},\"registration\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:legalIdentifier:2\",\"type\":\"LegalIdentifier\",\"spatial\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country/SWE\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/country\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"notation\":\"country\",\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Sweden\"}},\"notation\":\"SE202100287401\"},\"homepage\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:webResource:1\",\"type\":\"WebResource\",\"contentURL\":\"http://www.umu.se/english/?languageId=1\"}}},\"grade\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:note:4\",\"type\":\"Note\",\"noteLiteral\":{\"en\":\"Pass\"}},\"idVerification\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/supervision-verification/70be69aaf9\",\"type\":\"Concept\",\"inScheme\":{\"id\":\"http://data.europa.eu/snb/supervision-verification/25831c2\",\"type\":\"ConceptScheme\"},\"prefLabel\":{\"en\":\"Supervised with ID Verification\"}},\"specifiedBy\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:learningAssessmentSpec:1\",\"type\":\"LearningAssessmentSpecification\",\"gradingScheme\":{\"id\":\"urn:epass:gradingScheme:1\",\"type\":\"GradingScheme\",\"description\":{\"en\":\"Grades are awarded on a scale from 1 to 10. Grades from 1 to 5.4 (Bachelor) / 5.9 (Master\u2019s) indicate a FAIL. Grades from 5.5 (Bachelor) / 6.0 (Master\u2019s) to 10 indicate a PASS.\\n1. Very bad\\n2. Bad\\n3. Low\\n4. Insufficient\\n5. Almost sufficient \\n6. Sufficient\\n7. Ample sufficient \\n8. Good \\n9. Very good \\n10. Excellent\"},\"title\":{\"en\":\"National grading\"}},\"language\":{\"id\":\"http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/language/E